description: Republicans improved their lot in the Senate but were foiled by Democrats in a few key states.
title: The Senate Races
title_page: The Senate Races - The New York Times
text: Rand Paul, a Tea Party-backed Republican candidate in Kentucky, was elected to the United States Senate on Tuesday, the first big victory of the night for the Tea Party in what was a precursor of big gains in Congress for the Republican Party. Mr. Paul with his wife, Kelley, at an election night party in Bowling Green, Ky.
